          <!-- Conclusion -->
          <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Excavation Success = Planning + Safety</h2>
            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
              Every excavation collapse is preventable. Every utility strike is avoidable. Every settlement failure 
              can be prevented. The difference between a successful excavation and a disaster is planning, proper 
              shoring, and never taking shortcuts on safety.
            </p>
            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
              In Toronto's challenging soils - clay that swells, high water tables, unknown fill - assume the worst 
              and protect accordingly. The cost of proper shoring is nothing compared to a collapse. The time for 
